<div class="post-content">

<h2>Gameplay Mechanics</h2>

<h3>The Fuse System</h3>
<p>Forget the classic FNAF power bar. Animatronic Memories replaces it with a fuse-based system that fundamentally changes how you manage resources. Your office door has a meter that fills up while it's closed. Let it max out and a fuse blows. Lose three fuses and the door is permanently stuck open — which means certain death. This prevents the old strategy of just camping the door shut until 6 AM, forcing you to time your closures carefully and take calculated risks.</p>

<h3>The Animatronics</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Bonnie &amp; Chica</strong> (Night 1+): The classic duo attacks through the right door. Close it when you spot them, but watch that fuse meter.</li>
    <li><strong>Freddy</strong> (Night 2+): Hides in the darkness and targets the fuse box directly. If he reaches it, total blackout — instant death. He also attacks through the door, making him a double threat.</li>
    <li><strong>Foxy &amp; Anne</strong> (Night 3+): Attack from Pirate Cove through the left window, which you close manually by holding it shut. Foxy is slow (peg leg), but Anne is significantly faster. Both are loud enough to hear coming.</li>
    <li><strong>Harley the Puppet</strong> (Night 4+): The most complex animatronic. She can jam your cameras with interference — find her and hit the radio button to drive her away, or lose a fuse. She can also crawl through the kitchen ventilation duct, and if you don't catch her in time, it's an instant kill.</li>
</ul>

</div>

